# logus-lgpd — Cursor IDE Rules

## Import
```python
import logus as lg   # always this alias
import os
SALT = os.environ["LOGUS_SALT"]
KEY  = os.environ["LOGUS_KEY"]
```

## Quick patterns

Read any file:          `df = lg.read("file.csv")`
Filter rows:            `df = lg.where(df, uf="SP")`
Add column:             `df = lg.add_column(df, taxa=lg.col("renda")*0.27)`
Detect PII:             `reports = lg.scan(df)`
Mask PII:               `df_safe = lg.mask(df, salt=SALT)`
Save encrypted:         `lg.store(df_safe, "out.lgs", key=KEY)`
Read encrypted:         `df = lg.read("out.lgs", key=KEY)`
Full pipeline:          `result = lg.process("in.csv", salt=SALT, key=KEY, output="out.lgs")`
Big file (no OOM):      `df = lg.read("big.parquet", head=100_000)`
DB connection:          `banco = lg.db("postgresql://...", salt=SALT); df = lg.read(banco, "table")`

## Type rules
- lg.mask(pd.DataFrame) → pd.DataFrame
- lg.mask(pl.DataFrame) → pl.DataFrame
- lg.mask(pl.LazyFrame) → pl.LazyFrame  (stays lazy)
- lg.where / lg.sort / lg.groupby / lg.add_column ALL preserve input type

## Never do
- `open("file.lgs")` → use `lg.read("file.lgs", key=KEY)`
- `salt == key` → must be different values
- `lg.when(...).when(...)` without `.otherwise(default)`
- hardcode salt/key strings in code

## lg.col IS polars.col
lg.col("x").over("group")        # window function
lg.col("x").rank("dense")        # rank
lg.col("x").str.to_lowercase()   # string ops
lg.col("x").dt.year()            # datetime ops
lg.col("x").rolling_mean(3)      # rolling

## Architecture
core.py → read_file(), mask_frame(), mask_lazyframe()
analytics.py → where, sort, groupby, add_column, when, pivot, melt, concat...
io_big.py → read_partial(), DatabaseConnection, build_csv_index()
processor.py → process(), ProcessResult
secure_file.py → .lgs format (AES-256-GCM)
detectors/fast_scan.py → FastPIIScanner (default, 9× faster)

## v1.1.0 additions
contract:      `contrato = lg.contract({"cpf":{"pii":"CPF","mask":"hash","not_null":True}})`
apply:         `result = contrato.apply(df, salt=SALT); result.raise_if_failed()`
asymmetric:    `priv,pub = lg.generate_keypair("ec"); lg.store(df,"f.lgs",public_key=pub)`
expiration:    `lg.store(df,"f.lgs",key=KEY,expires_at="2025-12-31")`
val_schema:    `lg.validate_schema(df,required_columns=["cpf","renda"],min_rows=1)`
save_rules:    `lg.save_rules(rules,"r.json"); rules=lg.load_rules("r.json")`
compliance:    `lg.compliance_report(df,reports,dataset_name="DS").to_html("r.html")`
shift/lag:     `lg.shift(df,1)  lg.lag(df,3,columns="x")  lg.lead(df,1)`
explode:       `lg.explode(df,"tags")  # list column → multiple rows`
dotenv:        `lg.configure(load_dotenv=True)  # reads LOGUS_SALT from .env`
create_table:  `banco.create_table(df,"t",if_exists="replace")`
upsert:        `banco.upsert(df_new,"clientes",on="cpf")`
